content: Today is the summer solstice.. more hours of daylight than any other day of the year. Soo.. being that Florida is the Sunshine State, does Miami have more hours of sunlight today than NYC? The answer might surprise you! NYC will have 15 hours, 5 minutes of daylight. Miami will have 13 hours, 45 minutes of daylight -- 100 minutes LESS than NY. That's because the further north you go in the summer, the longer the hours of daylight. In fact, Seattle  will see nearly 19 hours of daylight today.. the sun will be up until 9:10pm Pacific Time! #abc7NY

content: Last night, I had the privilege of emceeing the Bishop's Humanitarian Award Dinner at Cipriani Wall Street to benefit Catholic Charities Brooklyn and Queens. 550 people attended and helped the organization raise $1.1 million. Over 93 cents of every dollar raised goes directly to help their clients. CCBQ is one of the largest multi-service nonprofit agencies in the nation.. offering 160 programs for people in need in Brooklyn and Queens.. from affordable housing to food assistance.. to counseling and education. They are truly a wonderful organization! #abc7NY
